@page "/about"

<PageTitle>About | Hugo Palafox</PageTitle>

<SectionContainer>
    <PageHeader
        Eyebrow="About"
        Title="Robotics & Automation Systems Engineer"
        Description="Designing and deploying robotics, PLC, and embedded systems for production automation." />

    <div class="content-grid">
        <article class="card prose">
            <h2>Professional Summary</h2>
            <p>
                Robotics & Automation Systems Engineer with end-to-end ownership across robotics integration,
                PLC controls, embedded edge systems, and industrial software. My work focuses on delivering
                reliable automation systems that operate consistently in real production environments.
            </p>

            <h2>Engineering Approach</h2>
            <p>
                I prioritize system behavior over individual components—defining interfaces early, validating
                against realistic failure modes, and optimizing for commissioning reliability instead of demo-only behavior.
            </p>

            <h2>Multidisciplinary Scope</h2>
            <p>
                My work spans mechanical integration boundaries, controls orchestration, embedded Linux deployment
                infrastructure, and OT-IT software services, allowing me to connect robotics, controls, edge systems,
                and software into production-ready solutions.
            </p>

            <h2>Industry Experience</h2>
            <p>
                Experience across automotive and advanced manufacturing environments, including battery manufacturing,
                automotive electronics, plastics and injection molding support equipment, and warehouse-scale automation systems.
                These environments required high-mix production, strict uptime reliability, and rapid deployment and launch execution.
            </p>
        </article>
    </div>
</SectionContainer>